article.description: Brittany McPhee scored 16 points and Lili Thompson had 15 and No. 15 Stanford cruised to an 80-49 win over Colorado on Friday night.
article.headline: McPhee leads No. 15 Stanford women past Colorado 80-49
article.linkText: McPhee leads No. 15 Stanford women past Colorado 80-49
article.story:
BOULDER, Colo. --  Brittany McPhee scored 16 points and Lili Thompson had 15 and No. 15 Stanford cruised to an 80-49 win over Colorado on Friday night.

Erica McCall  added 13 points and Kaylee Johnson 12 for the Cardinal (21-6, 11-4 Pac-12)

Jamee Swan made 9 of 10 shots and led Colorado (6-20, 1-14) with 25 points. Her teammates were 10 of 47 from the field. Kennedy Leonard had 13 points. The Buffaloes made 2 of 15 from 3-point range and shot 33 percent, the 21st time this season a Cardinal opponent failed to reach 40 percent.

Stanford led 15-13 after one quarter and 37-29 at the half. The Cardinal then shot 54 percent in the second half and outscored Colorado 43-20. Stanford finished at 49 percent, going 7 of 14 from 3-point range, and made 17 of 19 free throws.

---

This story has been corrected to show Stanford's nickname is Cardinal, not Cardinals.
